<br>
Dragon raids are really fun--dunno why exactly, since there is always a lot of standing around, stupid deaths, cries for clerics and enchanters and threats to call off the raid for lack thereof...but they are still fun--can't really explain why.<br>
<br>
Because of that, and becuase I think they'd be Even More Fun without all of the above, and with clearly defined loot policies (and yes I guess my vested interest here is seeing bards with white scales but--), I'd like to see the SGA step up to the plate--NOT, and I emphasize this--to take them down ourselves--but to lead some open raids.<br>
<br>
With the demand for the drops I don't think its entirely &quot;fair&quot; to hold closed raids for vox or naggy--but I would like to see a raid held with the principles that the SGA espouses.<br>
